  p260: "Matt Prater is one of the longest-tenured kickers in NFL history, famous for holding the record for the longest field goal ever made. His 2025 projection with Buffalo is low, reflecting his advanced age but continued ability to contribute when called upon.",

  // ===== D/STs (p261-p292) =====
  p261: "The Buffalo Bills defense has emerged as one of the NFL's most fearsome units, combining a relentless pass rush with a ball-hawking secondary that generates turnovers at an elite rate. They project as the top fantasy D/ST in 2025 with league-leading sack totals and a stingy scoring defense.",
  p262: "The Philadelphia Eagles defense has been a dominant force in recent seasons, anchored by a star-studded defensive line and playmaking secondary. They project as a top-tier fantasy D/ST in 2025 with elite turnover production and the ability to limit opposing offenses.",
  p263: "The Baltimore Ravens defense carries on the franchise's storied tradition of hard-hitting, turnover-generating play on that side of the ball. They project as a premium fantasy D/ST in 2025 behind a deep front seven and opportunistic secondary.",
  p264: "The Denver Broncos defense has rebuilt into one of the league's more well-rounded units, generating consistent pressure and turnovers. They project as a strong fantasy D/ST option in 2025 with above-average production across all defensive categories.",
  p265: "The Minnesota Vikings defense has invested heavily in talent on that side of the ball, creating a unit that can take over games with turnovers and big plays. They project as a reliable high-end fantasy D/ST in 2025 with a strong secondary leading the way.",
  p266: "The Pittsburgh Steelers defense continues the franchise's legacy of elite defensive play, featuring a deep pass rush rotation and disciplined coverage unit. They project as a dependable fantasy D/ST option in 2025 with consistent week-to-week production.",
  p267: "The San Francisco 49ers defense has been one of the NFL's best when healthy, boasting top-tier talent at every level. They project as a strong fantasy D/ST in 2025, though the unit's ceiling is tied to the health of several key contributors.",
  p268: "The Detroit Lions defense has undergone a dramatic transformation, becoming one of the league's most improved units through aggressive investment in talent. They project as a solid fantasy D/ST in 2025 with upside if the young core continues to develop.",
  p269: "The Kansas City Chiefs defense has been a steady, reliable unit that benefits from playing with a lead in most games thanks to the team's elite offense. They project as a safe fantasy D/ST option in 2025 with favorable game scripts boosting their production floor.",
  p270: "The Houston Texans defense has rapidly improved as the team has added talent to complement their ascending offense. They project as a mid-tier fantasy D/ST in 2025 with upside tied to the development of their young defensive playmakers.",
  p271: "The Los Angeles Chargers defense has shown the ability to generate pressure and create turnovers under their current coaching staff. They project as a usable fantasy D/ST in 2025 with a solid pass rush anchoring the unit's production.",
  p272: "The Green Bay Packers defense has been rebuilding alongside the team's offensive youth movement, showing encouraging progress in recent seasons. They project as a mid-range fantasy D/ST in 2025 with a developing pass rush and improving secondary.",
  p273: "The Chicago Bears defense has a long history of excellence and has invested in talented front-seven players to restore that tradition. They project as a serviceable fantasy D/ST in 2025 with a strong defensive line providing a reliable floor.",
  p274: "The Dallas Cowboys defense has been inconsistent in recent seasons but retains enough talent to produce playmaking weeks. They project as a mid-tier fantasy D/ST in 2025 with boom-or-bust weekly variance.",
  p275: "The Cleveland Browns defense has been one of the team's strengths, featuring a talented pass rush led by their elite edge rushers. They project as a matchup-dependent fantasy D/ST in 2025 with upside against weaker offenses.",
  p276: "The New York Jets defense has been built around elite talent at the cornerback and edge rusher positions. They project as a streamable fantasy D/ST in 2025 with production dependent on generating turnovers.",
  p277: "The Tampa Bay Buccaneers defense has been a middle-of-the-pack unit in recent seasons, capable of occasional standout performances. They project as a low-end startable D/ST in 2025 best used in favorable matchups.",
  p278: "The Miami Dolphins defense has steadily improved but remains an average unit that struggles against the league's better offenses. They project as a fringe fantasy D/ST in 2025 best deployed as a matchup-based streamer.",
  p279: "The New Orleans Saints defense has fluctuated in recent years as the team has undergone roster turnover. They project as a below-average fantasy D/ST in 2025 with limited upside outside of plus matchups.",
  p280: "The Seattle Seahawks defense has been rebuilding since the departure of its Legion of Boom-era stars. They project as a back-end fantasy D/ST in 2025 with occasional streaming appeal in favorable home matchups.",
  p281: "The Cincinnati Bengals defense has taken a backseat to the team's high-powered offense in terms of roster investment. They project as a low-end fantasy D/ST in 2025 with modest production expected across the board.",
  p282: "The Washington Commanders defense is still in the process of building through the draft and free agency. They project as a below-average fantasy D/ST in 2025 with limited standalone value in most formats.",
  p283: "The Indianapolis Colts defense has been inconsistent as the team has focused on building around its offensive core. They project as a low-ceiling fantasy D/ST in 2025 best left on the waiver wire in most weeks.",
  p284: "The Los Angeles Rams defense has struggled with injuries and roster turnover in recent seasons, limiting its effectiveness. They project as a fringe fantasy D/ST in 2025 with streaming potential only in the best matchups.",
  p285: "The Atlanta Falcons defense has been one of the league's weaker units in recent years, lacking consistent playmakers at every level. They project as a low-end fantasy D/ST in 2025 with minimal weekly appeal.",
  p286: "The Arizona Cardinals defense is in the early stages of a rebuild, with young talent still developing across the roster. They project as a below-average fantasy D/ST in 2025 best avoided in most league formats.",
  p287: "The New York Giants defense has struggled alongside the team's overall rebuilding efforts, lacking the depth to produce consistently. They project as a bottom-tier fantasy D/ST in 2025 with very limited upside.",
  p288: "The Jacksonville Jaguars defense has underperformed relative to expectations, dealing with injuries and inconsistency. They project as a low-end fantasy D/ST in 2025 with little standalone value.",
  p289: "The Tennessee Titans defense has been in transition as the team has prioritized offensive improvements in recent drafts. They project as one of the weaker fantasy D/ST options in 2025 with below-average production expected.",
  p290: "The New England Patriots defense has declined from its recent peaks as the team undergoes a broader roster rebuild. They project as a bottom-tier fantasy D/ST in 2025 with minimal fantasy relevance.",
  p291: "The Las Vegas Raiders defense has been among the league's least productive units, lacking consistent pressure and turnover generation. They project as one of the weakest fantasy D/ST options in 2025.",
  p292: "The Carolina Panthers defense has struggled significantly in recent seasons as part of the team's broader rebuilding effort. They project as the lowest-ranked fantasy D/ST in 2025 with the fewest expected fantasy points.",
